This paper is primarily focused on evaluating the security of graphical patterns and PINs in Android devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the study involves human participants and their behavior in response to shoulder surfing attacks, which could also be classified under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of video simulations and live simulations also involves the use of technology to model and analyze human behavior, which could fall under social and information sciences (cs.SI) or cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the study involves analyzing the effectiveness of security measures, which could also fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
